a, build_result dict\n  - Expected: metadata.image field updated with build result\n  - Verify metadata saved to file\n\n- [ ] **T-014**: Test `_update_build_metadata()` - Merge with existing image data\n  - Setup: workspace with metadata containing existing image data\n  - Expected: new build result merged with existing data\n  - Verify merge behavior\n\n- [ ] **T-015**: Test `build()` - Successful local build\n  - Setup: complete workspace with Dockerfile, metadata\n  - Mock: all dependencies return success\n  - Expected: returns BuildResult dict with all fields\n  - Verify version incremented and metadata updated\n\n- [ ] **T-016**: Test `build()` - Version reversion on build failure\n  - Setup: workspace with version=\"1.0.0\"\n  - Mock: _build_local() raises RuntimeError\n  - Expected: version reverted to \"1.0.0\"\n  - Verify metadata saved with reverted version\n\n- [ ] **T-017**: Test `build()` - Cloud build mode\n  - Setup: workspace with build_mode=\"cloud\"\n  - Expected: calls _build_cloud() instead of _build_local()\n  - Verify build mode selection logic\n\n- [ ] **T-018**: Test `build()` - Missing metadata file\n  - Setup: workspace without metadata file\n  - Expected: raises FileNotFoundError\n  - Verify error handling for missing metadata\n\n- [ ] **T-019**: Test `build()` - Invalid build mode in metadata\n  - Setup: metadata with build_mode=\"invalid\"\n  - Expected: raises ValueError or handles gracefully\n  - Verify build mode validation\n\n### Unit Tests for DockerService\n\n- [ ] **T-020**: Create `test_docker_service.py` file structure\n  - Create test file: `tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Add TestDockerService class\n  - Configure pytest fixtures for Docker mocking\n\n- [ ] **T-021**: Test `check_docker_available()` - Docker available\n  - Mock: docker.from_env().ping() returns success\n  - Expected: returns True\n  - Verify Docker availability check\n\n- [ ] **T-022**: Test `check_docker_available()` - Docker unavailable\n  - Mock: docker.from_env().ping() raises DockerException\n  - Expected: returns False\n  - Verify error handling and logging\n\n- [ ] **T-023**: Test `build_image()` - Successful build\n  - Setup: valid dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name\n  - Mock: client.images.build() returns image and logs\n  - Expected: returns dict with image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time\n  - Verify build parameters passed correctly\n\n- [ ] **T-024**: Test `build_image()` - Build with custom tag\n  - Setup: tag=\"v1.0.0\"\n  - Expected: image built with correct tag\n  - Verify tag format in full_image_name\n\n- [ ] **T-025**: Test `build_image()` - Build with build arguments\n  - Setup: build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy\"}\n  - Expected: build args passed to Docker build\n  - Verify build arguments handling\n\n- [ ] **T-026**: Test `build_image()` - Docker unavailable\n  - Mock: check_docker_available() returns False\n  - Expected: raises RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available\")\n  - Verify prerequisite check\n\n- [ ] **T-027**: Test `build_image()` - Docker build failure\n  - Mock: client.images.build() raises DockerException\n  - Expected: raises RuntimeError with original exception\n  - Verify error propagation\n\n- [ ] **T-028**: Test `get_image_info()` - Get existing image info\n  - Mock: client.images.get() returns image with attrs\n  - Expected: returns dict with image_name, image_id, image_size, size_bytes\n  - Verify image ID truncated to 12 chars\n  - Verify size formatting\n\n- [ ] **T-029**: Test `get_image_info()` - Image not found\n  - Mock: client.images.get() raises DockerException\n  - Expected: returns empty dict (logged as warning)\n  - Verify graceful degradation\n\n- [ ] **T-030**: Test `_format_size()` - Size in bytes\n  - Input: 512\n  - Expected: \"512.00 B\"\n  - Verify size formatting for bytes\n\n- [ ] **T-031**: Test `_format_size()` - Size in KB\n  - Input: 2048\n  - Expected: \"2.00 KB\"\n  - Verify size formatting for KB\n\n- [ ] **T-032**: Test `_for