- [ ] **T-042**: Test `remove_image()` - Successful removal\n  - Mock: client.images.remove() returns success\n  - Expected: returns True\n  - Verify removal called with force=True\n\n- [ ] **T-043**: Test `remove_image()` - Removal failure\n  - Mock: client.images.remove() raises DockerException\n  - Expected: returns False (logged as warning)\n  - Verify graceful degradation\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **T-044**: Test end-to-end local build with Docker\n  - Setup: complete workspace with valid Dockerfile\n  - Mock: real Docker operations (or use test Docker daemon)\n  - Expected: successful build with valid image\n  - Verify: image created, metadata updated, version incremented\n\n- [ ] **T-045**: Test build with proxy in real environment\n  - Setup: workspace requiring proxy for dependencies\n  - Expected: build succeeds with proxy configuration\n  - Verify proxy build args used\n\n- [ ] **T-046**: Test build failure and recovery\n  - Setup: workspace with invalid Dockerfile\n  - Expected: build fails, version reverted\n  - Verify error handling and rollback\n\n- [ ] **T-047**: Test multiple sequential builds\n  - Setup: workspace, run build twice\n  - Expected: version increments correctly each time\n  - Verify version management across builds\n\n- [ ] **T-048**: Test build with different metadata versions\n  - Setup: workspace with various version formats\n  - Expected: each version format handled correctly\n  - Verify version increment rules\n\n### Test Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **T-049**: Add pytest fixtures for workspace setup\n  - Create fixtures for temporary workspaces\n  - Create fixtures for mock DockerService\n  - Create fixtures for mock MetadataService\n  - Ensure fixtures are reusable across tests\n\n- [ ] **T-050**: Configure test coverage reporting\n  - Add pytest-cov configuration\n  - Set coverage targets: build_runtime.py 90%+, docker_service.py 85%+\n  - Add coverage reporting to CI/CD pipeline\n\n- [ ] **T-051**: Add integration test markers\n  - Add pytest marker for integration tests\n  - Configure pytest to skip integration tests by default\n  - Add documentation for running integration tests\n\n- [ ] **T-052**: Add test data fixtures\n  - Create sample Dockerfiles for testing\n  - Create sample metadata files for testing\n  - Create sample workspace structures\n\n### Code Quality\n\n- [ ] **T-053**: Run linter on test files\n  - Run `ruff check tests/`\n  - Fix any linting issues\n  - Ensure code follows project style guidelines\n\n- [ ] **T-054**: Run type checker on test files\n  - Run `mypy tests/`\n  - Fix any type checking issues\n  - Ensure type hints are correct\n\n- [ ] **T-055**: Verify test documentation\n  - Add docstrings to all test classes and methods\n  - Document test purpose and expected behavior\n  - Ensure test names are descriptive\n\n### Verification Tasks\n\n- [ ] **T-056**: Run all tests and ensure 100% pass rate\n  - Run `pytest tests/`\n  - Verify all tests pass\n  - Review any failures and fix\n\n- [ ] **T-057**: Generate coverage report\n  - Run `pytest --cov=agentcube.runtime.build_runtime --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service`\n  - Verify coverage meets targets\n  - Add coverage badge if below target\n\n- [ ] **T-058**: Manual testing of build command\n  - Test `kubectl-agentcube build` with real workspace\n  - Test with proxy option\n  - Test with verbose option\n  - Verify error handling\n\n- [ ] **T-059**: Test error messages\n  - Test all error scenarios manually\n  - Verify error messages are user-friendly\n  - Verify error messages match design specifications\n\n- [ ] **T-060**: Document test execution\n  - Add test execution instructions to README\n  - Document how to run unit vs integration tests\n  - Document test prerequisites (Docker daemon)\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n- T-001 must be completed before T-002 through T-019\n- T-020 must be completed before T-021 through T-043\n- T-049 should be completed early to support other test tasks\n- T-044 through T-048 require Docker daemon and should be marked as integration tests\n- T-056 through T-060 are verification tasks that depend on all test implementation tasks\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All unit tests pass (T-001 through T-043)\n- [ ] All integration tests pass (T-044 through T-048)\n- [ ] Code coverage meets targets: build_runtime.py 90%+, docker_service.py 85%+\n- [ ] All linter and type checker checks pass\n- [ ] Manual testing confirms build command works as expected\n- [ ] Documentation is complete and accurate\n\n## Notes\n\n- Use pytest-mock for mocking dependencies\n- Use tempfile for temporary workspace creation\n- Integration tests should be marked with `@pytest.mark.integration`\n- Some tests may require actual Docker daemon (consider optional integration tests)\n- Follow existing test patterns from test_pack_runtime.py and test_metadata_service.py","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/tasks-AR-021.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py\">\nERROR [67:13] Argument of type \"float\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"value\" of type \"str\" in function \"__setitem__\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [99:27] Type \"float\" is not assignable to declared type \"int\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py":[{"range"